      <hedline>
        <hl1>People</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Courtney Kane</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Steve Dunkley is named executive creative director at Trone Advertising, Greensboro, NC; Nancy Rueth is named president at Presence Euro RSCG, New York (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Steve Dunkley was named to the vacant post of executive creative director at Trone Advertising, Greensboro, N.C. He had been vice president and creative director at the San Francisco office of FCB Worldwide, part of True North Communications.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Steve Dunkley was named to the vacant post of executive creative director at Trone Advertising, Greensboro, N.C. He had been vice president and creative director at the San Francisco office of FCB Worldwide, part of True North Communications.</p>
        <p>* Nancy Rueth was named president at Presence Euro RSCG, New York, part of the Euro RSCG Worldwide unit of Havas Advertising, succeeding Laura Schoen, who became president at the global health care practice of BSMG Worldwide, New York, part of True North Communications. Ms. Rueth had been managing director at Ogilvy Public Relations Worldwide, New York, part of the WPP Group, where she helped develop the health care practice.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
